### Automated Testing Strategy

```typescript
// Button.test.tsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';
import { axe, toHaveNoViolations } from 'jest-axe';
import { Button } from './Button';

expect.extend(toHaveNoViolations);

describe('Button', () => {
  // Visual tests
  it('renders all variants correctly', () => {
    const { container } = render(
      <>
        <Button variant="primary">Primary</Button>
        <Button variant="secondary">Secondary</Button>
        <Button variant="outline">Outline</Button>
      </>
    );
    expect(container).toMatchSnapshot();
  });

  // Interaction tests
  it('handles click events', () => {
    const handleClick = jest.fn();
    render(<Button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</Button>);

    fireEvent.click(screen.getByText('Click me'));
    expect(handleClick).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });

  // Accessibility tests
  it('meets accessibility standards', async () => {
    const { container } = render(<Button>Accessible Button</Button>);
    const results = await axe(container);
    expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
  });

  // Loading state tests
  it('shows loading spinner and disables when loading', () => {
    render(<Button isLoading>Loading</Button>);
    const button = screen.getByRole('button');

    expect(button).toBeDisabled();
    expect(screen.getByRole('button')).toContainHTML('svg');
  });
});
```

## Documentation Best Practices

Great documentation makes or breaks a design system:

### 1. Component Pages Should Include:

- **Overview**: What is this component and when to use it
- **Live Examples**: Interactive demos with code
- **Props API**: Complete TypeScript definitions
- **Accessibility**: ARIA attributes and keyboard support
- **Best Practices**: Do's and don'ts
- **Related Components**: Similar or complementary components

### 2. Documentation Structure

```markdown
# Button Component

## Overview
Buttons allow users to take actions with a single tap.

## Usage
\`\`\`tsx
import { Button } from '@company/design-system';

function App() {
  return <Button>Click me</Button>;
}
\`\`\`

## Variants
[Interactive examples]

## Props
| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| variant | 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'primary' | Button style |

## Accessibility
- Supports keyboard navigation
- ARIA labels for screen readers
- Focus states clearly visible

## Best Practices
‚úÖ Do: Use primary buttons for main actions
‚ùå Don't: Use more than one primary button per page
```
